quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  76,23,"That We, We descended on you the Koran descent"
  76,24,"So be patient for your Lord`s judgment/rule, and do not obey a sinner/criminal (insistent) disbeliever from them"
  76,25,And remember/mention your Lord (at) daybreaks/early mornings and (at) evening to sunset
  76,26,"And from the night, so prostrate to Him, and praise/glorify Him at night/nightly long"
  76,27,"That truly those love/like the worldly life/present, and they leave behind them a heavy day/time"
  76,28,"We, We created them and We strengthened/supported their bone structure/ties and joints/(strengths) , and if We willed/wanted/intended We exchanged/replaced their equivalent (by) an exchange/replacement"
  76,29,"That truly this (is) a reminder, so who wanted took/received a way/path to his Lord"
  76,30,"And you do not will/want except that (E) God wills/wants/intends, that truly God was/is knowledgeable, wise/judicious"
  76,31,"He enters whom He wills/wants in His mercy, and the unjust/oppressive, He prepared for them a painful torture"